Enum PowerManager.RunningLockType

  • All Implemented Interfaces:

    Enclosing class:
    PowerManager

    public static enum PowerManager.RunningLockType
extends Enum<PowerManager.RunningLockType>
    Enumerates the RunningLock types.

    Two RunningLock types are available: BACKGROUND, and PROXIMITY_SCREEN_CONTROL. BACKGROUND ensures that applications can run in the background. PROXIMITY_SCREEN_CONTROL determines whether to turn on or off the screen based on the proximity sensor.

      • PROXIMITY_SCREEN_CONTROL

        public static final PowerManager.RunningLockType PROXIMITY_SCREEN_CONTROL
        Indicates the lock that determines whether to turn on or off the screen based on the proximity sensor. For example, during a call, if the proximity sensor detects that the device is moving close to the user's ear, the screen turns off; if the proximity sensor detects that the device is moving away from the user's ear, the screen turns on.
